Apply Now: <a href="http://careerwebapp.us/sales-associate-841" rel="nofollow">http://careerwebapp.us/sales-associate-841</a><br>
<br>
Location:<br>
Bertrand's Old Town Music, Pasadena<br>
<br>
Bertrand's Music is a family music store where we all share a passion for music. Our main focus is band & orchestra instrument rentals, sales, repairs, and lessons. We are looking for a seasoned musician who has experience with classical sheet music, as we have one of the largest selections in California.  We have an immense variety, carrying the most sought after methods, to the hard to find international prints.<br>
<br>
<br>
We are a full-service music store and pride ourselves on customer service. We are also one of the top music stores in the country and have won several awards including Top 100 Music Store (6th year in a row) & California Small Business of the  Year. <br>
<br>
The Sales Associate is responsible to greet, sell, and provide superior customer service to each guest in a friendly and efficient manner. In addition, the Sales Associate will handle their assigned duties including but not limited to: presenting products to the customer, rotating product, clean & merchandise displays, cleaning store & instruments, receiving, stocking and display of musical products, & balance cash register sales.<br>
<br>
Job Duties:<br>
<br>
• Sheet music knowledge is required.  Ability to track down hard to find pieces is used daily.<br>
• Acknowledge, greet and engage guest upon entering Bertrand's Music<br>
• Exceed guest expectations for service and build a reputation for ultimate service<br>
• Be attentive at all times to guests and be ready to serve guests.<br>
• Ensure displays are clean, well merchandised, signs visible, and products are rotated.<br>
• Ability to inform guest of all musical products <br>
• Demonstrate positive, enthusiastic, committed and flexible attitude at all times, while promoting the importance of effective teamwork. (Ability to work weekends, especially Sundays)<br>
• Maintain positive working relationships through respectful, open and effective two-way communication with all coworkers, supervisors, and all management.<br>
• Excellent interpersonal and organizational skills, ability to prioritize and work effectively within a sometimes pressurized environment.<br>
• Practice safe work habits; maintain a high level of store cleanliness, organization, and a safe work environment.<br>
• General Knowledge of Band & Orchestra instruments is required.<br>
<br>
Hours: Part-time - 15-25 Hours a week to start.  Must have consistent weekly schedule.  Will not consider freelance/gigging musicians unless there is a FIRM commitment to store's schedule/needs. <br>
<br>
Skills/Qualifications: <br>
• A passion to work in the music industry & general knowledge of Band & Orchestra Instruments<br>
• Must enjoy and be able to succeed positively and work effectively in a fast-paced team environment.<br>
• Superior sheet music knowledge.<br>
• Knowledge of general accounting/cash register principles<br>
• Fluent in English and Spanish preferred.<br>
<br>
Interested and well-qualified candidates should send resumes along with a short paragraph about you and your sheet music knowledge. Please also include your availability.<br>
<br>
Apply Now: <a href="http://careerwebapp.us/sales-associate-841" rel="nofollow">http://careerwebapp.us/sales-associate-841</a>    </section>

